HEADWORD: Electioneer
<hw>E*lec`tion*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Electionered</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Electioneering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make interest for a
candidate at an election; to use arts for securing the election of a
candidate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A master of the whole art of <qex>electioneering</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

